data.name: QueryMostCollectivelyExpensiveQueries

data.name: QueryBasicTraceSummary
data.value: select * from (select min(CurrentTime) as [Trace Start Time], max(CurrentTime) as [Trace End Time] from [Table]) aa, (select count(*)[Queries Started] from [Table] where EventClass = 9) a, (select count(*)[Queries Completed] from [Table] where EventClass = 10) b, (select count(*)[Incomplete Queries] from [Table_QueriesAndCommandsIncludingIncomplete] where EventClass = -10) bb, (select sum(Duration)[Total Query Duration], avg(Duration)[Average Query Duration] from [Table] where EventClass = 10) e, (select( (select max(Duration) from (select TOP 50 percent Duration from [Table_QueriesAndCommandsIncludingIncomplete] where EventClass in (10, -10) and Duration > 0 order by Duration) as BottomHalf) + (select max(Duration) from (select TOP 50 percent Duration from [Table_QueriesAndCommandsIncludingIncomplete] where EventClass in (10, -10) and Duration > 0 order by Duration desc) as TopHalf) ) / 2 AS [Median Query Duration]) g, (select count(*)[Commands Started] from [Table] where EventClass = 15) c, (select count(*)[Commands Completed] from [Table] where EventClass = 16) d, (select count(*)[Incomplete Commands] from [Table_QueriesAndCommandsIncludingIncomplete] where EventClass = -16) dd, (select sum(Duration) [Total Command Duration], avg(Duration) [Average Command Duration] from [Table] where EventClass = 16) f, (select( (select max(Duration) from (select TOP 50 percent Duration from [Table_QueriesAndCommandsIncludingIncomplete] where EventClass in (16, -16) and Duration > 0 order by Duration) as BottomHalf) + (select max(Duration) from (select TOP 50 percent Duration from [Table_QueriesAndCommandsIncludingIncomplete] where EventClass in (16, -16) and Duration > 0 order by Duration desc) as TopHalf) ) / 2 AS [Median Command Duration]) h

data.name: QueryPossibleRunawaySessions
data.value: -- These sessions were active when the trace started and never showed any begin or end events. -- This can indicate the sessions were already active and remained active without ever completing. -- If heavy load isn't otherwise detectable in a trace, check with users of possible runaway sessions. select 'Existing Session' as EventClassName, convert(nvarchar(4000), StartTime, 21) StartTime, Duration as [Session Duration at TraceStart], ConnectionID, NTUserName, NTDomainName, DatabaseName, SPID, TextData as [Session Roles], ClientProcessID, ApplicationName, RequestProperties as [Session Properties] from [Table] where connectionid not in ( select connectionid from ( select connectionID, eventclass from [Table] group by connectionid, eventclass ) a where a.eventclass in (1, 2, 15, 16, 9, 10, 36, 38) and not ConnectionID is null ) and not databasename is null and eventclass = 42 order by rownumber

b.OriginalQueryEndRow is null then 'Request Incomplete' else convert(nvarchar(4000), b.OriginalQueryEndRow) end EndRow, b.OriginalQueryDuration Duration, case when EventClass in (-9, 9, 10, -10) then
